Responsibilities:
To provide servicing and repairs, conversions, factory testing, site commissioning and provide technical and troubleshooting support for in-house and on-site jobs.
Dismantle, service, repair, troubleshooting and assemble regulators and skids.
Perform all testing on regulators and functional test and commissioning of skids.
Manage contractors and suppliers, ensuring skids fabricated on schedule.
Conduct inspections of skids witnesses by third party agency/customers.
Prepare reports, documentation, maintain tools and equipments, housekeeping practices.
Requirements:
Diploma/ITC in Mechanical or Electro-Mechanical Engineering with at least 5 to 10 years working experience on service related jobs.
Possess drive and initiative.
Able to read and understand instruction manuals and understand mechanical drawings.
Basic understanding on work safety.